Subject: Election Forecasting and Polling
Snippet: Contingency analysis, TensorFlow tutorial for beginners, recommended IDEs for data scientists and much more! DataCamp ISSUE #66 â€” OCTOBER 9, 2018 Happy Tuesday! This week we're diving into
Message_body:
[

Contingency analysis, TensorFlow tutorial for beginners, recommended IDEs for data scientists and much more! Â  DataCamp ( https://www.datacamp.com ) Â  ISSUE #66 â€” OCTOBER 9, 2018 Â  Happy Tuesday! This week we're diving into contingency analysis in R, a TensorFlow tutorial for beginners, recommended IDEs for data scientists and much more! We also have a new episode of DataFramed! Andrew Gelman, professor of statistics and political science, and director of the Applied Statistics Center at Columbia University, speaks with Hugo about statistics, data science, polling, and election forecasting. Listen Now ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/podcast/election-forecasting-polling ) Â  ------------------- Community Top Posts ------------------- Â  1 ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/contingency-analysis-r ) ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Contingency Analysis using R ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/contingency-analysis-r ) ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Â  R PROGRAMMINGÂ Â |Â Â  Posted by vedabrata10 Â  Upvotes ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/contingency-analysis-r ) 15 In this tutorial, you'll learn with the help of an example how 'Contingency Analysis' or 'Chi-square test of independence works and also how efficiently you can run it using R. Â  2 ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/tensorflow-tutorial ) ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ Tensorflow Tutorial for Beginners ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/tensorflow-tutorial ) ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ Â  TENSORFLOWÂ Â |Â Â  Posted by talibkhweled Â  Upvotes ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/tensorflow-tutorial ) 14 In this TensorFlow beginner tutorial, you'll learn how to build a neural network step-by-step and how to train, evaluate and optimize it. Â  3 ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-implement-cnn-using-keras-step-by-step-epkonoygd1r ) ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Step-by-step Implementation of CNN using Keras ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-implement-cnn-using-keras-step-by-step-epkonoygd1r ) ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Â  CNNÂ Â |Â Â  Posted by rizwankhan19 Â  Upvotes ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-implement-cnn-using-keras-step-by-step-epkonoygd1r ) 14 In this module, you will check out the implementation of CNN using Keras on MNIST dataset and then you will compare the results with the regular neural network. Â  4 ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/pairs-trading-on-etf-epat-project-work-tqr52uv1fdn ) ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Pairs Trading on ETF EPAT Project Work ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/pairs-trading-on-etf-epat-project-work-tqr52uv1fdn ) ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Â  FINANCEÂ Â |Â Â  Posted by virajb Â  Upvotes ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/pairs-trading-on-etf-epat-project-work-tqr52uv1fdn ) 13 This project covers building a portfolio using 3 ETF pairs in oil (USO vs XLE), technology (XLK vs IYW), and financial sectors (XLF vs PSCF). Â  5 ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/lenet-5-a-classic-hello-world-cnn-architecture-8lwolq0mpzr ) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- LeNet-5: a classic, 'hello-world' CNN architecture ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/lenet-5-a-classic-hello-world-cnn-architecture-8lwolq0mpzr ) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Â  NEURAL NETWORKSÂ Â |Â Â  Posted by rizwankhan19 Â  Upvotes ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/lenet-5-a-classic-hello-world-cnn-architecture-8lwolq0mpzr ) 12 Yann LeCun proposed a neural network architecture for handwritten and machine-printed character recognition in the 1990s which he called LeNet-5. The architecture is straightforward and simple to understand which is why it is mostly used as the first step for teaching Convolutional Neural Networks. Â  6 ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/real-effective-exchange-rate-reer-3vfgzg96tr8 ) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Real Effective Exchange Rate (REER) ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/real-effective-exchange-rate-reer-3vfgzg96tr8 ) ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Â  FINANCEÂ Â |Â Â  Posted by virajb Â  Upvotes ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/real-effective-exchange-rate-reer-3vfgzg96tr8 ) 9 The real effective exchange rate (REER) is the weighted average of a country's currency in relation to a basket of other currencies.
